&lt;p&gt;At AKQA (part of WPP), we believe in the imaginative application of art and science to create a better future. With an entrepreneurial and collaborative approach, we design adaptive ideas, services and experiences that capture the imagination, delivering impressive returns for our clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Accounts Payable at AKQA works in the Administration and Management Control team, providing support to a wide range of operational tasks. You will be exposed to an international framework, supporting our European offices, and the working mechanisms of a structured, multinational Group.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At AKQA you will have access to world-renowned thought leadership from influential authors, athletes, artists and entrepreneurs. You will work in an environment which fosters a meritocratic culture and encourages ownership, and you will be surrounded by some of the brightest minds in their fields.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a Fixed Term Contract position for Maternity Cover for approximately for 9-12 months.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ROLE REQUIREMENTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accounts Payable:&amp;nbsp;Booking and processing supplier invoices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bank Reconciliation:&amp;nbsp;Recording and reconciling daily bank movements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;General Ledger Bookkeeping:&amp;nbsp;Recording general ledger and journal entries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expense Management:&amp;nbsp;Reviewing, verifying, and processing employee expense reports&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Master Data Management:&amp;nbsp;Setting up and maintaining new vendor and client accounts in the ERP system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Credit Card Management:&amp;nbsp;Tracking, reconciling, and recording credit card transactions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support on monthly reporting for the Financial Controller&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support on compliance review and documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALITIES AND CHARACTERISTICS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accuracy, integrity and the ability to work within specific deadlines are your keys to succeed in this role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a good understanding of accounting principles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a good knowledge of Excel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are willing to learn new tools (such as SAP, Matisse, documentation workflow)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are able to interact effectively at a professional level in both Italian and English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Driven by enthusiasm and willingness to work in a challenging and dynamic environment, you demonstrate proactiveness and accountability in every task you are assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a positive, collaborative spirit and a hands-on attitude&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Explore our extensive range of benefits&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.akqa.com/studios/italy/benefits/&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;here&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
