&lt;p&gt;The Creative team at AKQA (part of WPP) applies artistry and craftsmanship to strategic insight, bringing to life beautiful and technologically innovative ideas that move the world. From a variety of backgrounds and disciplines, our creatives are innately curious and strive to transform client challenges into groundbreaking, design-led solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Associate Creative Director (Art/Design) in our Amsterdam studio, you’ll inspire and lead a team to craft visually striking concepts and executions across CGI, motion design, and interactive media. With a foundation in art direction and deep expertise in production, you will direct specialized CGI artists and guide cross-disciplinary teams to create cinematic, technically precise, and emotionally-resonant work. From large-scale digital platforms and motion-led brand systems, to experimental storytelling powered by emerging tools, you’ll push the boundaries of what’s possible in digital creativity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’re a visionary creative leader who thinks like a filmmaker, builds like a technician, and creates like a storyteller, bringing together craft, innovation, and strategy to shape work that influences culture and elevates global brands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the AKQA team and based in our Amsterdam studio, you’ll work in an environment that fosters a dynamic and inclusive culture, enabled by our multidisciplinary approach and supported by some of the brightest minds in their field. You will report to the Creative Director and collaborate closely with team leads across the studio to continually inspire, innovate, and deliver work of the highest standard.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ROLE REQUIREMENTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver and lead award-winning work that meets client needs while influencing culture, blending art direction, design craft, and innovative use of technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct and Lead autonomous teams to bring cinematic vision, technical precision, and emotional storytelling into every project — thinking like a filmmaker, building like a technician, and creating like a storyteller.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and direct creative foundations in concepting art directions for production and motion graphics, ensuring ideas are strategically sound and visually compelling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to direct specialised CGI artists across animation, modelling, rigging, lighting, and compositing to maintain creative cohesion and quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply craft knowledge across CGI workflows, including modelling, lighting, animatics, grading, and retouching.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide hands-on expertise in retouching, compositing, grading, and finalising large-scale projects, guiding teams through complex production pipelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement advanced workflows such as EXR and ACES to ensure colour accuracy, consistency, and creative control.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to and lead the development of creative briefs, collaborating with clients and strategists to define opportunities and deliver visionary outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate across disciplines — including design, UX, and development — to integrate creativity, craft, and strategy seamlessly into final outputs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creatively lead new business pitches, presenting ideas and executions with confidence and clarity to global clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explore and implement AI-assisted workflows (e.g., ComfyUI with open-source models, LoRa training, Google partnerships) to push creative boundaries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate proficiency in editing (Adobe Premiere, After Effects), motion retouching (DaVinci), and emerging AI generation tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;QUALITIES AND CHARACTERISTICS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience at Associate Creative Director level or in a comparable art/design hybrid l

&lt;p&gt;At AKQA (part of WPP), we believe in the imaginative application of art and science to create ideas, products, and services that shape culture and drive meaningful outcomes. With an entrepreneurial and collaborative spirit, we design adaptive digital experiences that combine creativity, technology, and craft.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Delivery team sits at the heart of everything we do, ensuring work is delivered with precision, care, and commercial clarity. As Associate Programme Director for the Amsterdam office, you will lead a portfolio of complex, technology-led production programmes, including work shaped by AI and advanced CGI techniques.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will steward programme health end-to-end, balancing client ambition with agency capability, and building delivery models that are efficient, scalable, and future-facing. A key part of your role is helping evolve how AI-enabled workflows and modern production methods are applied across creative output.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will partner with clients as a trusted advisor, helping them navigate opportunity, complexity, and change - while leading multidisciplinary teams to deliver work of exceptional quality. In doing so, you will help shape how emerging technologies are meaningfully integrated into delivery practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based in central Amsterdam, you will collaborate across AKQA’s European studios in a culture built on ownership, curiosity, and craft, working alongside specialists who push the boundaries of creative technology and production.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ROLE &amp;amp; RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee a portfolio of projects (up to €2M), ensuring delivery on time, within budget, and aligned with AKQA standards across modern production and technology-enabled workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as primary client interface, building trusted senior relationships and advising on delivery strategy, including the effective use of AI and CGI where relevant.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead end-to-end delivery of complex digital programmes, ensuring excellence in execution, strong coordination across teams, and resolution of delivery challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own project financial performance, including budgeting, forecasting, and risk of overrun. Understand key cost drivers such as compute, tooling, and rendering, and contribute to portfolio-level planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define delivery approaches (fixed-price and T&amp;amp;M), leading scoping, estimation, scheduling, and SoW creation for complex programmes. Work closely with resource managers to ensure the right blend of specialist capability is applied.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with internal teams and clients to shape solutions and support new business opportunities, contributing to growth in AI-enabled production and advanced CGI work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and mitigate delivery risks, including ethical considerations, data usage, and production complexity. Maintain high standards through structured reviews and continuous improvement of tools and ways of working.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach and develop delivery teams, strengthening capability in modern production pipelines and emerging technologies, while fostering a high-performance, collaborative culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;QUALITIES &amp;amp; CHARACTERISTICS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive experience delivering complex digital production programmes in fast-moving, technology-led environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong grounding in CGI, animation, real-time, or generative production workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert understanding of programme and project management across Agile, Hybrid, and Waterfall approaches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to manage budgets, forecasting, and commercial delivery with strong attention to value and efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confident in working with business metrics

&lt;p&gt;At AKQA (part of WPP), we use the imaginative application of art and science to create beautiful ideas, products, and services. With an entrepreneurial and collaborative approach, we design adaptive digital services and content that capture the imagination, delivering impressive returns for our clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the heart of innovation, AKQA Sweden thrives. We are privileged to collaborate with a fantastic portfolio of clients, including Volvo Cars, Volvo Penta, H&amp;amp;M, Ikea, and Zimmer Biomet. Each partnership is a unique journey, a shared pursuit of creating transformative ideas, products, and services that resonate with their distinct needs and aspirations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working with the Delivery team connects you with talented experts from various backgrounds and experiences, who are passionate about ensuring work is delivered to the highest quality, on time, and that clients receive the greatest possible value from their investment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Associate Project Director in our Delivery team &amp;nbsp;at AKQA Sweden, you will play a critical role in leading and overseeing large workstreams, ensuring the successful delivery of complex and impactful assignments. Working across four distinct areas our Associate Directors have expertise in at least one area while being comfortable in all others.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Production: Leading complex film shoots, large-scale asset production for campaigns, or production of OOH assets at scale.&lt;br&gt;Projects: Leading international marketing campaigns in multiple markets, delivering digital and physical experiences.&lt;br&gt;Product: Leading complex design/technology-driven products, such as website re-platforming, App development for new revenue streams, or other large-scale product management.&lt;br&gt;Innovation: Implementing cutting-edge technologies and experimenting to find effective market fit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ROLE REQUIREMENTS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide mentoring and support to multiple project teams, ensuring the delivery of incredible customer experiences, including (but not limited to) websites, e-commerce, mobile apps, emerging technologies, films, products, or events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the successful setup, structure, and end-to-end delivery of multiple engagements involving technical, brand, marketing stakeholders, or environmental complexities, rollout plans in multiple countries, physical construction, or fixed deadlines.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish strong relationships with senior clients, partners, and multiple suppliers, ensuring the best outcomes for both clients and AKQA.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead on cross-department collaboration, knowledge sharing, and mentorship to promote a cohesive and high-performing work environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Iterate and teach tailored delivery approaches based on methodology or client need, ensuring alignment with business objectives and stakeholder expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal teams and clients to define and agree on the Scope of Work, ensuring engagements are clear, unambiguous, and effectively delivered.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead on client discussions regarding project realities, addressing open issues promptly and decisively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;QUALITIES AND CHARACTERISTICS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Significant&amp;nbsp; experience in managing diverse service delivery functions in a fast-paced environment, implementing innovative, interactive, and consumer-focused solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leads client sessions, resolving challenging discussions with senior client stakeholders, and building long-term relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert understanding of both waterfall and agile methodologies and when to use them.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience line managing multiple&amp;nbsp; team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt

&lt;p&gt;At AKQA (part of WPP) we believe in the imaginative application of art and science to create beautiful ideas, products and services. With an entrepreneurial and collaborative approach, we design adaptive digital services and applications that capture the imagination, delivering impressive returns for our clients.The Client Services team are entrepreneurs who champion clients and colleagues alike. With a keen sense for turning insight into opportunity, they are responsible for building relationships that foster commercial viability for our studio and our clients business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A Client Partner is a leadership position that requires expertise in transformational programs of work that deliver positive outcomes through products and service ecosystems, differentiated business models and the brand experience surrounding them. This role is central to driving the commercial health of the studio by ensuring the quality of AKQA deliverables, strong client satisfaction, and high employee engagement.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Client Partner will drive existing and new deliverables, lead pitches and pursue new growth opportunities for the studio. As a key member of the Client Services team, the Client Partner will play a pivotal role in providing leadership so that the CS team-members have the best environment for excellence. Reporting to the Client Services Director, you will partner with our Leads and interdisciplinary teams to create a work environment that fosters collaboration and innovation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Located on the Nieuwe Herengracht in central Amsterdam, you will also have access to our diverse network of specialists by collaborating across our European, Middle East and South African studios. You will work in an environment which fosters a meritocratic culture and encourages ownership, and you will be surrounded by some of the brightest minds in their fields.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Strategic Client Leadership&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grow organic business for key accounts - lead and mentor other Client Services team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sets strategy for account group - Strategic leadership of the internal team, setting the vision for the account, helping the team understand what needs to be delivered.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provides thought leadership to both clients and internal teams.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Makes the account team aware of senior level client challenges.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reports on client activity for executive meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provides senior clients and their boards with digital marketing expertise and innovative ideas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consults on their business challenges to deliver a positive difference to their bottom line through experience, entrepreneurialism and incisive thought.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Presents Strategic services offering to develop partnerships, new services and solutions that help client businesses exceed growth targets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Business Development&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify, engage, convert and scale new opportunities into long-term client relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead regional pitch responses and procurement processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop relationships with prospective clients, while maintaining existing client relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with discipline leads to create contract-winning proposals for current and prospective clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand the language of business to grow our CX, Venture and Product revenue targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Become a subject matter expert on topics that drive our clients business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a strong unders

&lt;p&gt;At AKQA we are working with a leading global car manufacturer. We are building a new team which will be bringing new vehicle models and annual updates to market through the client&#39;s digital vehicle configuration platform. We are hiring meticulous and analytical Config Analysts, to drive the critical function of data transformation and validation within this process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Configuration Analyst plays a central role in transforming raw product data into configurator-ready formats. This position ensures the accurate representation of vehicle specifications and market-specific content, from initial data ingestion and master build creation through to market localisation, rigorous quality assurance, and seamless handover to other parties. The Config Analyst manages complex datasets, applies intricate business rules, and collaborates across various internal and external stakeholders to deliver a flawless configurator experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ROLE REQUIREMENTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inputs and Master Build Creation:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect and process diverse data files from various client stakeholders / product teams, including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Product Specifications (Options Master): A complex Excel file detailing full specifications, standard/optional features, and initial business rules.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Add-ons / Accessories: Data on retailer-fit add-on parts, including availability and applicability rules.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pricing: Priced specification versions containing list prices for products and all optional features for specific markets.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Data: Technical Data Sheets from client engineering teams, listing technical specifications by variant.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other Data: Briefs for &quot;Curated Choices&quot; and &quot;Key Features,&quot; translation/copy decks, and digital/creative asset requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supplement and manipulate raw input data to optimize for the front-end application.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain a master &quot;International&quot; build using a proprietary configuration tool, capturing the full superset (150%) specification across all possible variants, features, and options for all markets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quality assurance testing of the master build in the configurator UI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Market Localisation, Quality Assurance, and Handover:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tailor the master build for individual markets by applying market-specific applicability rules (Standard, Optional, Not Available) based on the relevant section of the specifications master.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate market-specific pricing by loading pricing files to apply local currency and prices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement localised technical data and copy, including footer caveats and translations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply any unique local business rules that are specific to a market, such as tax calculations or legal disclaimers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform comprehensive Quality Assurance (QA) using the automated QA tool and manual checks to validate feature applicability, business rules, and overall accuracy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate market-specific configurator reviews with relevant client regional teams / market stakeholders, incorporating feedback and securing final sign-off.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage continuous collaboration and data handover to the technical partner using a JIRA ticketing system, capturing all briefs, amends, build history, and approvals for auditing purposes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide structured data files to the technical partner, including core Excel workbooks (data models), common files (shared rules, spe

&lt;p&gt;At AKQA we are working with a leading global car manufacturer. We are building a new team which will be bringing new vehicle models and annual updates to market through the client&#39;s digital vehicle configuration platform. We are hiring meticulous and analytical Config Analysts, to drive the critical function of data transformation and validation within this process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Configuration Analyst plays a central role in transforming raw product data into configurator-ready formats. This position ensures the accurate representation of vehicle specifications and market-specific content, from initial data ingestion and master build creation through to market localisation, rigorous quality assurance, and seamless handover to other parties. The Config Analyst manages complex datasets, applies intricate business rules, and collaborates across various internal and external stakeholders to deliver a flawless configurator experience.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ROLE REQUIREMENTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inputs and Master Build Creation:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect and process diverse data files from various client stakeholders / product teams, including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Product Specifications (Options Master): A complex Excel file detailing full specifications, standard/optional features, and initial business rules.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Add-ons / Accessories: Data on retailer-fit add-on parts, including availability and applicability rules.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pricing: Priced specification versions containing list prices for products and all optional features for specific markets.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Data: Technical Data Sheets from client engineering teams, listing technical specifications by variant.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other Data: Briefs for &quot;Curated Choices&quot; and &quot;Key Features,&quot; translation/copy decks, and digital/creative asset requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supplement and manipulate raw input data to optimize for the front-end application.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain a master &quot;International&quot; build using a proprietary configuration tool, capturing the full superset (150%) specification across all possible variants, features, and options for all markets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quality assurance testing of the master build in the configurator UI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Market Localisation, Quality Assurance, and Handover:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tailor the master build for individual markets by applying market-specific applicability rules (Standard, Optional, Not Available) based on the relevant section of the specifications master.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate market-specific pricing by loading pricing files to apply local currency and prices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement localised technical data and copy, including footer caveats and translations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply any unique local business rules that are specific to a market, such as tax calculations or legal disclaimers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform comprehensive Quality Assurance (QA) using the automated QA tool and manual checks to validate feature applicability, business rules, and overall accuracy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate market-specific configurator reviews with relevant client regional teams / market stakeholders, incorporating feedback and securing final sign-off.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage continuous collaboration and data handover to the technical partner using a JIRA ticketing system, capturing all briefs, amends, build history, and approvals for auditing purposes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide structured data files to the technical partner, including core Excel workbooks (data models), common files (shared rules, spe

&lt;p&gt;At AKQA (part of WPP), we believe in the imaginative application of art and science to create a better future. With an entrepreneurial and collaborative approach, we design adaptive ideas, services, and experiences that capture the imagination and deliver meaningful impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Creatives at AKQA fuse artistry and craftsmanship with strategic insight to build brands, products, campaigns, and experiences that earn attention and live in culture. They are storytellers and makers, working across disciplines to unlock new value for our clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Creative Team member in MENA, you will play an essential role in the strategy, conception, and execution of ideas spanning brand, experience, product, and innovation. Together, you will combine words and visuals into one cohesive creative system, driving work that is conceptually strong, beautifully crafted, and culturally relevant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will operate as a unit: thinking together, making together, and pushing each other to produce work that neither discipline could achieve alone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At AKQA, you will be surrounded by some of the brightest minds across design, technology, and creativity, with access to world-class thinking and an environment that rewards ambition, ownership, and craft.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ROLE REQUIREMENTS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead with creative hunger. Drive ideas from first spark to final execution with the energy of makers and the accountability of owners. Push for work that is braver, sharper, and built to matter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Think as one system. Unify art direction and writing into a single idea. No handovers, no silos, every output should feel like one voice expressed through multiple forms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Craft with obsession.&amp;nbsp;Words, visuals, motion, interaction; every detail matters. Whether it&#39;s a line, a layout, a script, or a prototype, the work should feel precise, intentional, and world-class.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tell stories that live everywhere. Shape narratives that translate across film, social, product, experience, and PR. Understand how ideas behave within local, regional, and global cultures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Think beyond the ad.&amp;nbsp;Create ideas that exist as acts, products, services, platforms, and content ecosystems. Use technology, AI, and innovation as creative tools, not decoration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make ideas PR-able by design.&amp;nbsp;Build work that earns attention. Ideas should be culturally relevant, conversation-worthy, and designed to travel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the process end-to-end.&amp;nbsp;From early concept to production and launch, drive the work through every stage. Know when to craft hands-on and when to lead from altitude.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate like modern creatives.&amp;nbsp;Work fluidly with strategists, designers, technologists, producers, and the wider AKQA network. Seek tension that sharpens the work, not comfort that softens it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Elevate the room.&amp;nbsp;Bring energy, references, and perspective that push the work forward. Mentor others, challenge thinking, and raise the creative standard around you.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Challenge the brief, intelligently.&amp;nbsp;Ask better questions. Find the tension. Push for the version of the work that will actually move people and create impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present with clarity and conviction.&amp;nbsp;Tell the story behind the work in a way that builds belief. Make clients feel the ambition, not just understand it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guard the quality.&amp;nbsp;Be accountable for everything that leaves the studio. Ensure every output reflects AKQA&#39;s global standard and your own creative integrity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;QUALITIES AND CHARACTERISTICS&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of relevant creative

&lt;p&gt;At AKQA (part of WPP)&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;we believe in the imaginative application of art and science to create beautiful ideas, products and services. With an entrepreneurial and collaborative approach, we design adaptive digital services and applications that capture the imagination, delivering impressive returns for our clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Designer working within the Marketing and PR team, you will create a range of considered and bespoke assets for our channels, ensuring the AKQA brand is expressed consistently and distinctively, from external, in-market channels to internal moments. The ideal candidate possesses strong communication skills, an impeccable design aesthetic, a demonstrated understanding of visual storytelling across both short form digital content and longer form narrative formats&amp;nbsp; and exceptional attention to detail.&lt;/p&gt;
